# Online Mail Promotion System — Cursor Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Vue 3 + Element Plus + Axios (SPA admin dashboard)
- Backend: Spring Boot 3.x or FastAPI (TBD)
- Database: MySQL 8.0 (Volcano Cloud RDS)
- Cache/Queue: Redis (Volcano Cloud)
- Storage: Volcano Cloud TOS (S3-compatible object storage)
- AI: Doubao Open Platform API
- Email: SMTP for sending, IMAP for reply polling
- Real-time: WebSocket + Browser Notification API

## Architecture Rules
- B/S architecture deployed on Volcano Cloud ECS behind HTTPS
- Doubao API keys and email credentials must be encrypted at rest in MySQL, never exposed to frontend
- Frontend never directly calls Doubao API — all AI requests go through backend
- File uploads go to TOS first, then backend parses asynchronously
- Background jobs (IMAP polling, batch sending) run as scheduled tasks separate from the API server
- WebSocket used for real-time push of new reply notifications and sending progress

## Frontend Rules
- Use Element Plus components for all UI; maintain consistent Chinese-language admin interface
- Excel upload must show validation progress and allow downloading error-row files
- Email editor supports HTML rich text with live preview
- Sending progress displayed in real-time (success/fail counts with failure reasons)
- Message center with read/unread filter and browser desktop notifications

## Backend Rules
- All customer PII (emails, names, phone numbers) handled with encryption at rest
- SMTP sending must rotate across multiple accounts with configurable rate limits per account
- IMAP polling must match replies to original sent emails by customer email address
- AI-generated email content must pass sensitive-word filter before storage/display
- Full audit log for: login, file upload, batch send, AI generation, config changes

## Security Rules
- Token-based authentication with role-based access (super admin / operator / read-only viewer)
- Upload file type whitelist — block executables and scripts
- TOS object ACLs must be private; generate pre-signed URLs for frontend download
- API endpoints must validate ownership of resources (no IDOR)
- Never log API keys, passwords, or customer emails in plaintext
